# Learned Patterns: Embeddings

*Auto-generated by Hippocampus MOS from 3 error patterns in hippocampus.*
*Last updated: 2026-03-24 01:29*

## Pattern 1

**ERROR: import cycle not allowed: embedding imports app imports embedding**

- Context:  Adding Prometheus metrics directly in app package, then importing app from embedding package
- Why:  Prometheus metric variables defined in internal/app/prometheus.go, but embedding/openai.go needed to reference them, creating app->embedding->app cycle
- Fix:  Move all Prometheus metrics to separate internal/metrics package that both app and embedding can import without cycles
- Prevention:  Always put shared instrumentation (metrics, tracing) in a leaf package with no internal dependencies
- File: `internal/metrics/prometheus.go`

## Pattern 2

CRITICAL BUG FIX (2026-03-18): Embeddings were never loaded from DB in SearchSimilar queries. scanEpisodic/scanSemantic/scanProcedural did not SELECT or Scan the embedding column. This caused: 1) cosineSimilarity(query, candidate) = 0 always (40% of score formula dead), 2) redundancyPenalty = 0 always (submodular maximization degraded to top-K), 3) all composite scores clustered at 0.46-0.50 (only recency + importance). Fix: added embedding::text to SELECT in SearchSimilar/SearchGlobal/SearchByTaskType, created collectXxxWithEmbedding() functions that scan embedding as string, added decodeVector() in pgvector.go to parse pgvector text format back to []float32. After fix: scores range 0.66-0.75, correct memories selected per query, redundancy penalty actively filters duplicates (7 candidates → 2 selected).

